

***Project Title: 
Pizza Sales Performance Analysis using SQL

***Objective:
To analyse transactional pizza sales data using SQL in order to generate actionable business insights related to revenue, customer demand patterns, and product performance.

***Business Context 
This project simulates a real-world scenario where a food business aims to
Improve revenue performance
Optimise operational efficiency
Understand customer purchasing behaviour

*** Dataset Description

Data Source: Kaggle dataset

Tables Used:
orders – order-level data
order_details – line-item details
pizzas – pricing and size
pizza_types – category and product info

***Key Fields:

Order ID, Pizza ID, Quantity,Order Date & Time,Price,Category & Size

***Data Model Relationships

One-to-many: orders → order_details
Many-to-one: order_details → pizzas
Many-to-one: pizzas → pizza_types

***Analytical Approach

Data understanding and relational mapping
Query-based exploration using SQL
Aggregation and trend analysis
Business insight generation
Result interpretation for decision-making.

***Key Findings 

Peak demand occurs between 18:00–21:00, indicating strong evening consumption patterns
Classic category pizzas account for the highest share of total sales
Weekend revenue is significantly higher (~20–25%) compared to weekdays
A small subset of products (top 3 pizzas) contributes disproportionately to overall revenue (Pareto effect)
Larger pizza sizes contribute more to revenue, despite lower order frequency.

***Business Recommendations

Increase staffing during peak evening hours to improve service efficiency
Promote high-margin pizzas through targeted offers
Introduce weekday discounts to balance demand
Bundle large-size pizzas to maximise average order value.

